quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  33,7,"And [remember] when We took from the prophets their covenant and from you [O Prophet], and from Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, son of Mary; We took from them a solemn covenant"
  33,8,"so that He may question the truthful about their truthfulness, and He has prepared for the disbelievers a painful punishment"
  33,9,"O you who believe, remember Allah’s favor upon you when [enemy] forces came against you, but We sent against them a violent wind and forces that you could not see. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  33,10,"When they came upon you from above you and from below you, and your eyes grew wild [in horror], and the hearts reached the throats, and you began to entertain various thoughts about Allah"
  33,11,There the believers were tested and were severely shaken
  33,12,"And [remember] when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, “Allah and His Messenger did not promise us but delusion!”"
  33,13,"And [remember] when a group of them said, “O people of Yathrib, you cannot withstand [the enemy attack], so go back.” Another group of them asked the Prophet’s permission to leave, saying, “Our homes are exposed,” even though they were not exposed; they only wanted to flee"
  33,14,"If the enemy were to enter the town upon them from all sides, and they were asked to abandon faith, they would have done it and would not have shown hesitation in it except a little"
  33,15,"They had already made a covenant with Allah earlier that they would not turn and flee, and the covenant of Allah will surely be questioned about"